10. AI, AGENT, AUTONOMY, AND ASSURANCE CLAIM BOUNDARY

IX-MissionProof is a research-oriented AI-assurance and authority-control
prototype.

The Software is not represented as:

(a) artificial general intelligence;

(b) consciousness, sentience, personhood, or an autonomous legal authority;

(c) an independently validated safety, security, governance, compliance, or
certification system;

(d) a replacement for qualified human judgment, professional review,
regulatory review, safety engineering, security engineering, legal review,
acquisition authority, mission authority, or operational command;

(e) proof that any model, agent, autonomous system, software system, workflow,
organization, or mission is safe, secure, compliant, trustworthy,
production-ready, procurement-ready, deployment-ready, or mission-ready; or

(f) a guarantee that unsafe, incorrect, deceptive, unauthorized, abusive, or
harmful behavior will be detected, prevented, contained, or corrected.

Software output is not evidence merely because the Software produced it.

An evidence record is not independently verified proof merely because the
Software stored, linked, hashed, signed, scored, or displayed it.

A claim is not approved merely because the Software evaluated it.

A passing test is not certification.

A generated assurance case is not regulatory, safety, security, legal,
procurement, or mission approval.

A simulated outcome is not an observed real-world outcome.

A prediction is not an observation.

A memory record is not truth merely because it was retained.

A model, agent, or autonomous system does not possess authority merely because
it has capability, produced an output, passed an automated gate, or was assigned
an automated role.

Human authority remains required for all Consequential Actions and for all
commercial, production, operational, government, regulated, safety-relevant,
security-relevant, customer-facing, and mission-facing use.

Independent evidence, qualified review, applicable testing, and authorized
human decisions remain necessary wherever the circumstances require them.

